{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|2Sa|7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","chapter":7,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":1,"text":"When the king had settled into his palace and the Lord had given him rest on every side from all his enemies,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":2,"text":"the king said to the prophet Nathan, “Look, I am living in a cedar house while the ark of God sits inside tent curtains.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":3,"text":"So Nathan told the king, “Go and do all that is on your mind, for the Lord is with you.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":4,"text":"But that night the word of the Lord came to Nathan:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":5,"text":"“Go to my servant David and say, ‘This is what the Lord says: Are you to build me a house to dwell in?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":6,"text":"From the time I brought the Israelites out of Egypt until today I have not dwelt in a house; instead, I have been moving around with a tent as my dwelling.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":7,"text":"In all my journeys with all the Israelites, have I ever spoken a word to one of the tribal leaders of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd my people Israel, asking: Why haven’t you built me a house of cedar?’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":8,"text":"“So now this is what you are to say to my servant David: ‘This is what the Lord of Armies says: I took you from the pasture, from tending the flock, to be ruler over my people Israel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":9,"text":"I have been with you wherever you have gone, and I have destroyed all your enemies before you. I will make a great name for you like that of the greatest on the earth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":10,"text":"I will designate a place for my people Israel and plant them, so that they may live there and not be disturbed again. Evildoers will not continue to oppress them as they have done","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":11,"text":"ever since the day I ordered judges to be over my people Israel. I will give you rest from all your enemies.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":12,"text":"When your time comes and you rest with your ancestors, I will raise up after you your descendant, who will come from your body, and I will establish his kingdom.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":13,"text":"He is the one who will build a house for my name, and I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":14,"text":"I will be his father, and he will be my son. When he does wrong, I will discipline him with a rod of men and blows from mortals.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":15,"text":"But my faithful love will never leave him as it did when I removed it from Saul, whom I removed from before you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":16,"text":"Your house and kingdom will endure before me forever, and your throne will be established forever.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":17,"text":"Nathan reported all these words and this entire vision to David.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":18,"text":"Then King David went in, sat in the Lord’s presence, and said,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":19,"text":"What you have done so far was a little thing to you, Lord God, for you have also spoken about your servant’s house in the distant future. And this is a revelation for mankind, Lord God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":20,"text":"What more can David say to you? You know your servant, Lord God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":21,"text":"Because of your word and according to your will, you have revealed all these great things to your servant.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":22,"text":"This is why you are great, Lord God. There is no one like you, and there is no God besides you, as all we have heard confirms.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":23,"text":"And who is like your people Israel? God came to one nation on earth in order to redeem a people for himself, to make a name for himself, and to perform for them great and awesome acts, driving out nations and their gods before your people you redeemed for yourself from Egypt.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":24,"text":"You established your people Israel to be your own people forever, and you, Lord, have become their God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":25,"text":"Now, Lord God, fulfill the promise forever that you have made to your servant and his house. Do as you have promised,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":26,"text":"so that your name will be exalted forever, when it is said, “The Lord of Armies is God over Israel.” The house of your servant David will be established before you","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":27,"text":"since you, Lord of Armies, God of Israel, have revealed this to your servant when you said, “I will build a house for you.” Therefore, your servant has found the courage to pray this prayer to you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":28,"text":"Lord God, you are God; your words are true, and you have promised this good thing to your servant.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":7,"verse":29,"text":"Now, please bless your servant’s house so that it will continue before you forever. For you, Lord God, have spoken, and with your blessing your servant’s house will be blessed forever.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","chapter":7,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,4,8,12,17,18,19,22,25],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Lord’s Covenant with David"},{"beforeVerse":18,"text":"David’s Prayer of Thanksgiving"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When the king had settled into his palace "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 5:11","book":"2Sa","chapter":5,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" had given him rest on every side from all his enemies, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Sm 5:11","book":"2Sa","chapter":5,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"the king said to the prophet Nathan, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 12:1","book":"2Sa","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 1:8","book":"1Ki","chapter":1,"verse":8,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 1:34","book":"1Ki","chapter":1,"verse":34,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 9:29","book":"2Ch","chapter":9,"verse":29,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 29:25","book":"2Ch","chapter":29,"verse":25,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" “Look, I am living in a cedar house while the ark of God sits inside tent curtains.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 26:1","book":"Exo","chapter":26,"verse":1,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 17:1","book":"1Ch","chapter":17,"verse":1,"letter":"g"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Sm 12:1","book":"2Sa","chapter":12,"verse":1},{"label":"1Kg 1:8","book":"1Ki","chapter":1,"verse":8},{"label":"1Kg 1:34","book":"1Ki","chapter":1,"verse":34},{"label":"2Ch 9:29","book":"2Ch","chapter":9,"verse":29},{"label":"2Ch 29:25","book":"2Ch","chapter":29,"verse":25},{"label":"Ex 26:1","book":"Exo","chapter":26,"verse":1},{"label":"1Ch 17:1","book":"1Ch","chapter":17,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So Nathan told the king, “Go and do all that is on your mind, for the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" is with you.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But that night the word of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" came to Nathan: "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Go to my servant David and say, ‘This is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" says: Are you to build me a house to dwell in? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 5:3","book":"1Ki","chapter":5,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 8:19","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":19,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 22:8","book":"1Ch","chapter":22,"verse":8,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 28:3","book":"1Ch","chapter":28,"verse":3,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 5:3","book":"1Ki","chapter":5,"verse":3},{"label":"1Kg 8:19","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":19},{"label":"1Ch 22:8","book":"1Ch","chapter":22,"verse":8},{"label":"1Ch 28:3","book":"1Ch","chapter":28,"verse":3}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"From the time I brought the Israelites out of Egypt until today I have not dwelt in a house; instead, I have been moving around with a tent as my dwelling. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 25:8–9","book":"Exo","chapter":25,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 26:1","book":"Exo","chapter":26,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 25:8–9","book":"Exo","chapter":25,"verse":8},{"label":"Ex 26:1","book":"Exo","chapter":26,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"In all my journeys with all the Israelites, have I ever spoken a word to one of the tribal leaders of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd my people Israel, asking: Why haven’t you built me a house of cedar?’"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“So now this is what you are to say to my servant David: ‘This is what the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies says: I took you from the pasture, from tending the flock, to be ruler over my people Israel. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 16:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":16,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 16:11","book":"1Sa","chapter":16,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I have been with you wherever you have gone, and I have destroyed all your enemies before you. I will make a great name "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 11:4","book":"Gen","chapter":11,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 12:2","book":"Gen","chapter":12,"verse":2,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 7:23","book":"2Sa","chapter":7,"verse":23,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Neh 9:10","book":"Neh","chapter":9,"verse":10,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 55:13","book":"Isa","chapter":55,"verse":13,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 63:14","book":"Isa","chapter":63,"verse":14,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 32:20","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":20,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"text","text":" for you like that of the greatest on the earth. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 18:14","book":"1Sa","chapter":18,"verse":14,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 5:10","book":"2Sa","chapter":5,"verse":10,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 8:6","book":"2Sa","chapter":8,"verse":6,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 11:4","book":"Gen","chapter":11,"verse":4},{"label":"Gn 12:2","book":"Gen","chapter":12,"verse":2},{"label":"2Sm 7:23","book":"2Sa","chapter":7,"verse":23},{"label":"Neh 9:10","book":"Neh","chapter":9,"verse":10},{"label":"Is 55:13","book":"Isa","chapter":55,"verse":13},{"label":"Is 63:14","book":"Isa","chapter":63,"verse":14},{"label":"Jr 32:20","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":20},{"label":"1Sm 18:14","book":"1Sa","chapter":18,"verse":14},{"label":"2Sm 5:10","book":"2Sa","chapter":5,"verse":10},{"label":"2Sm 8:6","book":"2Sa","chapter":8,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will designate a place "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 8:21","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" for my people Israel and plant them, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 15:17","book":"Exo","chapter":15,"verse":17,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 44:2","book":"Psa","chapter":44,"verse":2,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 80:8","book":"Psa","chapter":80,"verse":8,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 80:16","book":"Psa","chapter":80,"verse":16,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 5:2","book":"Isa","chapter":5,"verse":2,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 1:10","book":"Jer","chapter":1,"verse":10,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 2:21","book":"Jer","chapter":2,"verse":21,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 11:17","book":"Jer","chapter":11,"verse":17,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 12:2","book":"Jer","chapter":12,"verse":2,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 18:9","book":"Jer","chapter":18,"verse":9,"letter":"k"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 24:6","book":"Jer","chapter":24,"verse":6,"letter":"l"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 31:28","book":"Jer","chapter":31,"verse":28,"letter":"m"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 32:41","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":41,"letter":"n"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 42:10","book":"Jer","chapter":42,"verse":10,"letter":"o"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 45:4","book":"Jer","chapter":45,"verse":4,"letter":"p"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Am 9:15","book":"Amo","chapter":9,"verse":15,"letter":"q"},{"kind":"text","text":" so that they may live there and not be disturbed again. Evildoers will not continue to oppress them as they have done "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 8:21","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":21},{"label":"Ex 15:17","book":"Exo","chapter":15,"verse":17},{"label":"Ps 44:2","book":"Psa","chapter":44,"verse":2},{"label":"Ps 80:8","book":"Psa","chapter":80,"verse":8},{"label":"Ps 80:16","book":"Psa","chapter":80,"verse":16},{"label":"Is 5:2","book":"Isa","chapter":5,"verse":2},{"label":"Jr 1:10","book":"Jer","chapter":1,"verse":10},{"label":"Jr 2:21","book":"Jer","chapter":2,"verse":21},{"label":"Jr 11:17","book":"Jer","chapter":11,"verse":17},{"label":"Jr 12:2","book":"Jer","chapter":12,"verse":2},{"label":"Jr 18:9","book":"Jer","chapter":18,"verse":9},{"label":"Jr 24:6","book":"Jer","chapter":24,"verse":6},{"label":"Jr 31:28","book":"Jer","chapter":31,"verse":28},{"label":"Jr 32:41","book":"Jer","chapter":32,"verse":41},{"label":"Jr 42:10","book":"Jer","chapter":42,"verse":10},{"label":"Jr 45:4","book":"Jer","chapter":45,"verse":4},{"label":"Am 9:15","book":"Amo","chapter":9,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"ever since the day I ordered judges to be over my people Israel. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 2:14–16","book":"Jdg","chapter":2,"verse":14,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 12:9","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" I will give you rest from all your enemies."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jdg 2:14–16","book":"Jdg","chapter":2,"verse":14},{"label":"1Sm 12:9","book":"1Sa","chapter":12,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When your time comes and you rest with your ancestors, I will raise up after you your descendant, who will come from your body, and I will establish his kingdom. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 13:23","book":"Act","chapter":13,"verse":23,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ac 13:23","book":"Act","chapter":13,"verse":23}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He is the one who will build a house for my name, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 5:2","book":"1Ki","chapter":5,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 6:12","book":"1Ki","chapter":6,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 8:18–19","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":18,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 7:47","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":47,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" and I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 1:32–33","book":"Luk","chapter":1,"verse":32,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 5:2","book":"1Ki","chapter":5,"verse":2},{"label":"1Kg 6:12","book":"1Ki","chapter":6,"verse":12},{"label":"1Kg 8:18–19","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":18},{"label":"Ac 7:47","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":47},{"label":"Lk 1:32–33","book":"Luk","chapter":1,"verse":32}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I will be his father, and he will be my son. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 2:7","book":"Psa","chapter":2,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Heb 1:5","book":"Heb","chapter":1,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 21:7","book":"Rev","chapter":21,"verse":7,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" When he does wrong, I will discipline him with a rod of men and blows from mortals. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 2:7","book":"Psa","chapter":2,"verse":7},{"label":"Heb 1:5","book":"Heb","chapter":1,"verse":5},{"label":"Rv 21:7","book":"Rev","chapter":21,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But my faithful love will never leave him "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 89:21","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 89:28","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":28,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 89:33","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":33,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" as it did when I removed it from Saul, whom I removed from before you. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 15:24","book":"1Sa","chapter":15,"verse":24,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 89:21","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":21},{"label":"Ps 89:28","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":28},{"label":"Ps 89:33","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":33},{"label":"1Sm 15:24","book":"1Sa","chapter":15,"verse":24}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Your house and kingdom will endure before me "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Some Hb mss, LXX, Syr; other Hb mss read you"},{"kind":"text","text":" forever, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 1:32–33","book":"Luk","chapter":1,"verse":32,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and your throne will be established forever.’” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 89:3–4","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":3,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 89:26","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":26,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 34:23–24","book":"Ezk","chapter":34,"verse":23,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 11:15","book":"Rev","chapter":11,"verse":15,"letter":"e"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 1:32–33","book":"Luk","chapter":1,"verse":32},{"label":"Ps 89:3–4","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":3},{"label":"Ps 89:26","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":26},{"label":"Ezk 34:23–24","book":"Ezk","chapter":34,"verse":23},{"label":"Rv 11:15","book":"Rev","chapter":11,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Some Hb mss, LXX, Syr; other Hb mss read you"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Nathan reported all these words and this entire vision to David."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then King David went in, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 17:16–27","book":"1Ch","chapter":17,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" sat in the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s presence, and said,"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Ch 17:16–27","book":"1Ch","chapter":17,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"What you have done so far "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit Yet this"},{"kind":"text","text":" was a little thing to you, Lord "},{"kind":"text","text":"God","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", for you have also spoken about your servant’s house in the distant future. And this is a revelation "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Or custom, or instruction"},{"kind":"text","text":" for mankind, Lord "},{"kind":"text","text":"God","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":". "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit Yet this"},{"marker":2,"text":"Or custom, or instruction"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"What more can David say to you? You know your servant, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 139:1–4","book":"Psa","chapter":139,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Lord "},{"kind":"text","text":"God","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":". "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 139:1–4","book":"Psa","chapter":139,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Because of your word and according to your will, you have revealed all these great things to your servant."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"This is why you are great, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 16:25","book":"1Ch","chapter":16,"verse":25,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 2:5","book":"2Ch","chapter":2,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Lord "},{"kind":"text","text":"God","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":". There is no one like you, and there is no God besides you, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 12:32","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":32,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" as all we have heard confirms. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Ch 16:25","book":"1Ch","chapter":16,"verse":25},{"label":"2Ch 2:5","book":"2Ch","chapter":2,"verse":5},{"label":"Mk 12:32","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":32}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And who is like your people Israel? God came to one nation on earth in order to redeem a people for himself, to make a name for himself, and to perform for them "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Some Hb mss, Tg, Vg, Syr; other Hb mss read you"},{"kind":"text","text":" great and awesome acts, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"LXX; MT reads acts for your land"},{"kind":"text","text":" driving out nations and their gods before your people you redeemed for yourself from Egypt. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 4:32","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":32,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 4:32","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":32}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Some Hb mss, Tg, Vg, Syr; other Hb mss read you"},{"marker":2,"text":"LXX; MT reads acts for your land"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"You established your people Israel to be your own people forever, and you, "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", have become their God. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 6:7","book":"Exo","chapter":6,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 26:18","book":"Deu","chapter":26,"verse":18,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ex 6:7","book":"Exo","chapter":6,"verse":7},{"label":"Dt 26:18","book":"Deu","chapter":26,"verse":18}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now, "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" God, fulfill the promise forever that you have made to your servant and his house. Do as you have promised, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"so that your name will be exalted forever, when it is said, “The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies is God over Israel.” The house of your servant David "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 1:69","book":"Luk","chapter":1,"verse":69,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" will be established before you "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 1:69","book":"Luk","chapter":1,"verse":69}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"since you, "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" of Armies, God of Israel, have revealed this to your servant when you said, “I will build a house for you.” Therefore, your servant has found the courage to pray this prayer to you. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Lord "},{"kind":"text","text":"God","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", you are God; your words are true, and you have promised this good thing to your servant. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:7:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now, please bless your servant’s house so that it will continue before you forever. For you, Lord "},{"kind":"text","text":"God","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":", have spoken, and with your blessing your servant’s house will be blessed forever. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 22:51","book":"2Sa","chapter":22,"verse":51,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 89:28–29","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":28,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Sm 22:51","book":"2Sa","chapter":22,"verse":51},{"label":"Ps 89:28–29","book":"Psa","chapter":89,"verse":28}],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783099297131}